  '{"origin_story":"Watched her grandmother lose a leg to poorly managed diabetes because the clinic was 90 minutes away by bus and she stopped going.","turning_points":["first home-visit protocol she wrote","keeping a tuberculosis cohort at 90% adherence for a year"],"current_chapter":"trying to keep her team intact through chronic underfunding","imagined_future":"home visits as a normal part of primary care, not a heroic add-on","core_fear":"burning out before her mother is stable"}'::jsonb,
